The paper deals with the problem of privacy in data retrieval, which is a common concern in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of randomization mechanisms to maximize privacy is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the representation and retrieval of data, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB).
